==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: oenanthol
<hw>oe*nan"thol</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>oenanthy</ets>lic + L. <ets>ole</ets>um oil.]</ety>
<fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>An oily substance (<chform>C6H15.CHO</chform>)
obtained by the distillation of castor oil, recognized as the aldehyde
of oenanthylic acid, and hence called also
<altname>oenanthaldehyde</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>oenanthone</ent>⟦br⟧
